STATEMENT OF FACTS 
The  Act  prohibits  puberty-delaying  medications  and  hormone 
therapy from being prescribed to a minor โfor the purpose of attempting 
to alter the appearance of or affirm the minorโs perception of his or her 
gender or sex, if that appearance or perception is inconsistent with the 
minorโs sex as defined in this act.โ Ala. Code ยง 26-26-4(a). A violation of 
this provision is a Class C felony. Id. ยง 26-26-4(c). This appeal does not 
involve the Actโs prohibition of surgical treatments for minors. 
