This appeal centers around section 4(a)(1)โ(3) of Alabamaโs 
Vulnerable Child Compassion and Protection Act (the โActโ).  Sec-
tion 4(a)(1)โ(3) of the Act states that โno person shall engage in or 
causeโ the prescription or administration of puberty blocking med-
ication or cross-sex hormone treatment to a minor โfor the purpose 
of attempting to alter the appearance of or affirm the minorโs per-
ception of his or her gender or sex, if that appearance or perception 
is inconsistent with the minorโs sex.โ  Thus, section 4(a)(1)โ(3) 

